ge manifest declares requests; a lockfile or caller policy grants a subset.\"}, :dependencies {:rule \"Every dependency entry must resolve to a lock entry before safe-build.\", :allow-kinds [:repo :registry :local], :registry \"Name/version records must resolve to signed manifest CID plus repo RID.\", :repo \"Repo refs must resolve through a signed repo journal to a commit/tree CID.\", :local \"Local path deps are development-only and non-reproducible unless locked by tree CID.\"}, :package-kinds {:rule \"Packages should be split by capability and contract boundary, not by a vague core/extension distinction.\", :allow-kinds [:library :adapter :schema-contract :tool :component], :library \"Pure code/data API with no implicit host capability.\", :adapter \"Integration package that binds two or more libraries or schema contracts, e.g. slides-office.\", :schema-contract \"Lexicon/schema/IR contract package. Consumers depend on the contract CID, not a runtime implementation.\", :tool \"CLI or development tool package.\", :component \"Executable or Wasm component package.\"}, :contracts {:rule \"A dependency on a data shape should prefer a schema-contract package with a locked manifest CID.\", :provides \"Packages may declare schema, lexicon, WIT, EDN IR, or API surfaces they provide.\", :consumes \"Packages may declare schema, lexicon, WIT, EDN IR, or API surfaces they consume.\", :wire \"Kotoba-owned app/resource APIs that cross a host or network boundary should expose Transit wire surfaces as wire.kotoba.* keywords.\", :adapter-rule \"Adapter packages carry integration dependencies explicitly; base libraries should not import optional adapters.\"}}"}]